{
  "texts": [
    "The role of RAG is particularly critical in dynamically typed languages, such as Python, due to the absence of explicit type information.",
    "Frameworks such as TypeTest address the context gap in dynamic language test generation by constructing a knowledge base containing code summaries and existing tests, using RAG to dynamically retrieve information on types and parameter construction [88].",
    "Recent empirical work quantifies the coverage gains provided by RAG and the associated trade-offs regarding cost and robustness across different knowledge sources [125].Regarding the selection of sample strategies, our systematic review reveals a clear trend where zero-shot learning serves as the predominant approach.",
    "Among all studies employing prompt engineering, 76 rely exclusively on the zero-shot strategy.",
    "This prevalence is primarily attributed to its ease of implementation, making it the preferred choice for the rapid validation of ideas."
  ]
}